<li><a href="/wiki/Robert_K._Merton" title="Robert K. Merton">Merton, Robert K.</a>. 1959. <i>Social Theory and Social Structure. Toward the codification of theory and research</i>, Glencoe: Ill. (Revised and enlarged edition) <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book">. <a href="/wiki/Online_Computer_Library_Center" title="Online Computer Library Center">OCLC</a> <a href="http://worldcat.org/oclc/4536864" class="external text" title="http://worldcat.org/oclc/4536864" rel="nofollow">4536864</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=&amp;rft_id=info:oclcnum/4536864&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Sociology"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><a href="http://www.camden.rutgers.edu/~wood/207socimagination.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.camden.rutgers.edu/~wood/207socimagination.htm" rel="nofollow">Mills, C. Wright, The Sociological Imagination,1959</a><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book">. <a href="/wiki/Online_Computer_Library_Center" title="Online Computer Library Center">OCLC</a> <a href="http://worldcat.org/oclc/165883" class="external text" title="http://worldcat.org/oclc/165883" rel="nofollow">165883</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=&amp;rft_id=info:oclcnum/165883&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Sociology"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><a href="http://ddl.uwinnipeg.ca/res_des/files/readings/cwmills-intel_craft.pdf" class="external text" title="http://ddl.uwinnipeg.ca/res_des/files/readings/cwmills-intel_craft.pdf" rel="nofollow">C. Wright Mills,Intellectual Craftsmanship Advices how to Work fore young Sociologist</a></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFMitchell2007.2C_originally_published_in_1968">Mitchell, Geoffrey Duncan (2007, originally published in 1968). <i>A Hundred Years of Sociology: A Concise History of the Major Figures, Ideas, and Schools of Sociological Thought</i>. New Brunswick, NJ: Transaction Publishers. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780202361680" class="internal">ISBN 9780202361680</a>. <a href="/wiki/Online_Computer_Library_Center" title="Online Computer Library Center">OCLC</a> <a href="http://worldcat.org/oclc/145146341" class="external text" title="http://worldcat.org/oclc/145146341" rel="nofollow">145146341</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=A+Hundred+Years+of+Sociology%3A+A+Concise+History+of+the+Major+Figures%2C+Ideas%2C+and+Schools+of+Sociological+Thought&amp;rft.aulast=Mitchell&amp;rft.aufirst=Geoffrey+Duncan&amp;rft.au=Mitchell%2C+Geoffrey+Duncan&amp;rft.date=2007%2C+originally+published+in+1968&amp;rft.place=New+Brunswick%2C+NJ&amp;rft.pub=Transaction+Publishers&amp;rft_id=info:oclcnum/145146341&amp;rft.isbn=9780202361680&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Sociology"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Robert_A._Nisbet" title="Robert A. Nisbet" class="mw-redirect">Nisbet, Robert A.</a> 1967. <i>The Sociological Tradition</i>, London, Heinemann Educational Books. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1560006676" class="internal">ISBN 1-56000-667-6</a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book">. <a href="/wiki/Online_Computer_Library_Center" title="Online Computer Library Center">OCLC</a> <a href="http://worldcat.org/oclc/26934810" class="external text" title="http://worldcat.org/oclc/26934810" rel="nofollow">26934810</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=&amp;rft_id=info:oclcnum/26934810&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Sociology"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
